ne pr-4 text-17 font-bold md:text-17">The SEC’s contested climate rule is on hold.</div><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup inline font-fkroman text-gray-33 dark:text-gray-ef [&amp;_a]:relative [&amp;_a]:z-10  [&amp;_a:hover]:text-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-underline-blurple dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:text-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-underline-franklin [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-blurple dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-franklin">Just weeks after finalizing it, the SEC announced a stay on the <a href="/2024/3/7/24093354/sec-climate-disclosure-rule-legal-challenges">landmark rule</a> that would push big public companies to divulge financial risks they face from climate change and share data on their greenhouse gas emissions. </p><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup mt-12 font-fkroman text-gray-33 dark:text-gray-ef [&amp;_a]:relative [&amp;_a]:z-10  [&amp;_a:hover]:text-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-underline-blurple dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:text-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-underline-franklin [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-blurple dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-franklin">While trying to find middle ground, the SEC wound up <a href="/2024/3/7/24093354/sec-climate-disclosure-rule-legal-challenges">pissing off</a> industry groups opposing disclosures <em>and</em> environmental groups who said the rule didn’t create enough transparency for investors.  <br>The SEC (in an emailed statement) says the “stay will facilitate the orderly judicial resolution of [legal] challenges and allow the court of appeals to focus on deciding the merits.”</p><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup mt-12 font-fkroman text-gray-33 dark:text-gray-ef [&amp;_a]:relative [&amp;_a]:z-10  [&amp;_a:hover]:text-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-underline-blurple dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:text-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-underline-franklin [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-blurple dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-franklin"></p><br/></div><div class="pt-12"><d